config PAYLOAD_CRABEFI
	bool "CrabEFI"
	depends on ARCH_X86
	help
	  Select this option if you want to build a coreboot image
	  with a CrabEFI payload.

	  CrabEFI is a minimal UEFI implementation written in Rust,
	  designed to run as a coreboot payload. It implements just
	  enough UEFI to boot Linux via shim/GRUB2 or systemd-boot.

	  See https://github.com/ArthurHeymans/CrabEFI for more information.
